.BK "Source Code Product Read Me First"
.H 1 "Preface"
This document introduces
the documentation for the UNIX System V/386 Release 4 Version 4 
Source Code Product (SCP) and directs the reader to the appropriate tape
directories and documents for additional start-up information.
This document describes:
.BL
.LI
the components of the Source Code Product
.LI
how to extract the documents from tape and print them
.LE
.H 2 "Notation Conventions"
Whenever the text includes examples of output from the computer and/or
commands entered by you, we follow the standard notation scheme
that is common throughout UNIX system documentation.
.BL
.LI
All computer input and output is shown in 
\f4constant width\fP font.
Examples of input include command names, option letters and words,
environment variables, filenames and directory names.
Examples of output include
diagnostics, error messages, and program output.
.LI
All substitutables, that is, parameters that are meant to be replaced by an
actual value, are shown in \f2italic font\fP.
.LE
